1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,369
The following exercises will help.

2
00:00:03,840 --> 00:00:06,609
Practice trading minds exercises.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,210
Situation.

4
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:10,849
Giving someone work instructions.

5
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:17,090
For best results, ask yourself, Looking at this from the viewpoint of someone who is new to this,

6
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:19,009
have I made myself clear?

7
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:20,530
Situation.

8
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:22,449
Writing an advertisement.

9
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:30,129
For best results, ask yourself, If I were a typical prospective buyer, how would I react to this ad?

10
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:33,249
Situation, telephone manners.

11
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:41,009
For best results, ask yourself, if I were the other person, what would I think of my telephone voice and manners?

12
00:00:41,760 --> 00:00:43,570
Situation, gift.

13
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:49,889
For best results, ask yourself, is this gift something I would like or is it something he will like?

14
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:52,369
Often there is an enormous difference.

15
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:55,970
Situation, the way I give orders.

16
00:00:56,160 --> 00:01:03,330
For best results, ask yourself, would I like to carry out orders if they were given to me the way I give them to others?

17
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,369
Situation, child discipline.

18
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:11,650
For best results, ask yourself, if I were the child, considering his age,

19
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:15,889
experience, and emotions, how would I react to this discipline?

20
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,609
Situation, my appearance.

21
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:25,090
For best results, ask yourself, what would I think of my superior if he were dressed like me?

22
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,050
Situation, preparing a speech.

23
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:35,889
For best results, ask yourself, considering the background and interests of the audience, what would I think of this remark?

24
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:38,450
situation, entertainment.

25
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:44,290
For best results, ask yourself, if I were my guests, what kinds of food,

26
00:01:44,290 --> 00:01:47,410
music, and entertainment would I like best?

27
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:52,609
Put the trading minds principle to work for you.

28
00:01:52,609 --> 00:01:53,970
1.

29
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,770
Consider the other person's situation.

30
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:59,729
Put yourself in his shoes, so to speak.

31
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:06,930
Remember, his interests, income, intelligence, and background may differ considerably from yours.

32
00:02:06,930 --> 00:02:08,210
2.

33
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:13,810
Now ask yourself, if I were in his situation, how would I react to this?

34
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:16,369
Whatever it is you want him to do.

35
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:17,729
3.

36
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:22,609
Then take the action that would move you if you were the other person.

37
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,609
Leadership rule number two.

38
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:27,489
Think.
